Hypopygium (
Figs. 14–17
, 
22–25
). Tergite IX with 19–25 setae on each side and with an anal point 132–140 μm long apically with peg 36–38 μm long (
Fig. 24
). Laterosternite IX with 9–11 setae. Transverse sternapodeme 336–340 μm long. Phallapodeme 152–172 μm long. Median aedeagal lobe 144–180 μm long, widest medially, then tapering abruptly and with the apex forming a sharp hook; lateral aedeagal lobe 168–188 μm long (
Figs. 16–17
). Gonocoxite 340–400 μm long. Gonostylus 248–280 μm long, with megaseta 10–12 μm long. HR 1.35–1.43.
